The paper focuses on multi-object tracking in a complex scene captured by a single camera, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves joint learning of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and temporally constrained metrics, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the creation of a large-scale dataset, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
